commit_message: Began AssembleT_250+.pl Version 1.0 for longer Illumina read assemblies
Added more warnings and sanity checks to AssembleT

AssembleG.pl Version 1.3

AssembleG.pl Version 1.3 fixed bug in merge template (missing mkdir command)

AssembleT.pl Version 1.2 04/25/14

AssembleT.pl Version 1.2 now runs Velvet Version 1.2.10 and Oases Version 0.2.08. Both Velvet and Oases were compiled to accept kmer values as long as 255 to accomedate longer illumina reads.

AssembleG.pl Version 1.2 

AssembleG.pl Version 1.2 now uses abyss-1.3.7 and this version of ABySS was compiled to accept kmers as long as 255 to accommodate longer illumina reads

AssembleT.pl Version 1.1

AssembleT.pl Version 1.1 fixed bug in writing special characters in a
web address

AssembleG.pl Version 1.1

AssembleG.pl Version 1.1 fixed bug in writing line to export abyss
paths recursively
add assembly metric generation and prinseq summary

Update fasta2fastq.pl

New Usage: fasta2fastq [base filename minus '.fasta' and '.qual']

Create fasta2fastq.pl

Script converts FAST and QAUL files to FASTQ format. It is a slight modification of a script posted to SeqAnwsers http://seqanswers.com/forums/showthread.php?t=2775

Update run_abyss.pl

Fixed bug in name=ing of paired end libraries and added line 42 as an example of a run with single end libraries
added a script to convert illumina headers and remove broken pairs from illumina data

perl run_abyss.pl for multi k-mer assemblies, merging assemblies, and generated assembly stats

This script runs an installation of ABySS-1.3.4 on beocat. Step 1 is
the assembly of multiple single k-mer assemblies. Step 2 is the merging
of these single k-mer assemblies by running ABySS on reads and the
unitigs from the multi-kmer assemblies. Step 3 writes a script to
calculate N25,N50,N75, cumulative scaffold length, number of scaffolds
for all assemblies.

Summarize read length etc before and after cleaning for multiple files

This script takes output log files from prinseq (v prinseq-lite-0.20.3)
and outputs summary cleaning metrics to either pre_post_clean_reads.csv.
changed permissions for master and output filename

assembly_quality_stats_for_multiple_assemblies.pl

This script runs a slightly modified version of Joseph Fass'
Count_fasta.pl (original available at
http://wiki.bioinformatics.ucdavis.edu/index.php/Count_fasta.pl ) on a
fasta file from each assembly. It then creates comma separated file
called assembly_metrics.txt listing the N25,N50,N75, cumulative contig
length, and number of contigs for each assembly.

Merges Abyss assemblies of various kmer values

Script to merge ASSEMBLIES of illumina LJD libraries
http://ngs-expert.com/tag/long-jumping-distance-libraries/ using
parameters listed on
http://manpages.ubuntu.com/manpages/raring/en/man1/abyss-pe.1.html.
This script runs on beocat
updated readme to reflect the new folder

Added brief descriptions of the scripts

Many scripts call software that is executable for all users on Beocat.
